<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:lang="en" xml:id="struct-columns">
    <teiHeader>
        <fileDesc>
            <titleStmt>
                <title>Columns</title>
                <respStmt>
                    <resp/>
                    <name/>
                </respStmt>
                <respStmt>
                    <resp/>
                    <name/>
                </respStmt>
            </titleStmt>
            <publicationStmt><p/></publicationStmt>
            <sourceDesc><p/></sourceDesc>
        </fileDesc>
    </teiHeader>
    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="content">
                <div type="leiden">
                <cit type="interpretive">
                    <quote>ᵃ[1st col] – ᵇ[2nd col]</quote><!-- apices!!!!!!!!!!!! -->
                </cit>
                <cit type="diplomatic">
                    <quote>ᵃ[1st col] – ᵇ[2nd col]</quote><!-- apices!!!!!!!!!!!! -->
                </cit>
            </div>
            <div type="explanation">
                <p>Should be used for labels and sigla.
                    Note: the <att>n</att>'s value is here alphabetical, in order to differentiate the <gi>cb</gi> from the <gi>lb</gi> in apparatus and commentary:
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                        <cb n="a"/>[text]
                        <cb n="b"/>[text]
                    </egXML>
                </p>
                <p>
                    The transformation will separate with a – the content of each column, and to each column will be assigned the letter (printed in superscript) used as <att>n</att>’s attribute (the stylesheet can handle a max of 4 columns [a,b,c,d]):    
                    <cit>
                        <quote>ᵃ(Ὁ ἅγιος) Νι – ᵇκόλ(αος)</quote><!-- apices!!!!!!!!!!!! -->
                    </cit>
                </p>
            </div>
            </div>
            <div type="responsibility">
                <listBibl>
                    <bibl>
                        <respStmt>
                            <resp>Author</resp>
                            <name>Alessio Sopracasa</name>
                        </respStmt>
                        <respStmt>
                            <resp>Author</resp>
                            <name>Martina Filosa</name>
                        </respStmt>
                    </bibl>
                </listBibl>
            </div>
            <div type="version">
                <p>SigiDoc version: 1.0</p>
            </div>
